                            <span class="bg-base-color mt-3 mx-auto mx-lg-0 sep-line-thick"></span>
                            <p class="mt-3 text-base">Our first date was the next day after that dinner with friends. Being already head over hills in love with Helen, we spend the whole day together. We walked, talked, laughed, cycled over the city…had dinner on the beach…everything was just perfect. We couldn’t let each other go and it was then when I understood she would become my wife one day. - Andrew</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="carousel-cell align-items-center justify-content-center no-gutters row w-100">
                    <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-5">
                        <img data-flickity-lazyload="/img/love-story/love-story-4.jpg" alt="" class="lazyload img-fluid" />
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-7 pl-lg-5 pt-5 pt-lg-0 text-center text-lg-left">
                        <div class="pl-lg-3">
                            <span class="d-block font-alt2 title-small">First Kiss</span>
                            <span class="bg-base-color mt-3 mx-auto mx-lg-0 sep-line-thick"></span>
                            <p class="mt-3 text-base">It happened on our first date. I remember I was so nervous, even though I felt safe and comfortable together with Andrew. He organized us a fantastic dinner at the seaside. When I got cold, he gave me his jacket and drow me home. After saying our goodbyes, just as I started to walk away from him, he grabbed my hand and pulled me close to him. Then he kissed me. I was smiling the entire night after. – Helen</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="carousel-cell align-items-center justify-content-center no-gutters row w-100">
                    <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-5">
                        <img data-flickity-lazyload="/img/love-story/love-story-3.jpg" alt="" class="lazyload img-fluid" />
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-7 pl-lg-5 pt-5 pt-lg-0 text-center text-lg-left">
